  "graph_rag": {
    "answer": "**Sauti** is the son of Lomaharshana, a learned man \u201cwell\u2011versed in the Puranas\u201d who appears at the beginning of the Mah\u0101bh\u0101rata. In the opening section he is the one who approaches the ascetics in the forest of Naimi\u015ba and, after being received with respect, **narrates the story of the Mah\u0101bh\u0101rata\u2019s composition**. He explains how Vy\u0101sa composed the epic, how Ganesha was appointed as its scribe, and recounts the background of the text\u2019s transmission to the sages and to the king Janamejaya. Thus, Sauti serves as the **narrator and introducer** of the Mah\u0101bh\u0101rata in its opening.  \n\n*Sources: chunk_002 (Sauti\u2019s introduction and dialogue with the sages) and chunk_004 (his explanation of Vy\u0101sa, Ganesha, and the Mah\u0101bh\u0101rata\u2019s origin).*",
